(1) package.json File Included In The Project And Has 2 Benefits
----------------------------------------------------------------
==> Let's You Manage The Dependencies Of The Project
==> Helps To Add Script That Help With Intial Build Of Project

(2) Create [package.json] File
-------------------------------
==> npm init
==> Hit Enter For Every Thing 

(3) Create [package.json] Without Asking Questions
---------------------------------------------------
==> [npm init --yes] Or [npm init -y]


(4) Set Default Values For package.json Before Creating It
-----------------------------------------------------------
==> npm config set init-author-name "Magdy Mohammed"  // Set Package.json Default Author Name
==> npm set init-license "MIT" // Set Package.json Default License Name
==> npm init -y

(5) Get Default Values Of Package.json
---------------------------------------
==> npm config get init-author-name // Get Package.json Default Author Name
==> npm get init-license  // Get Package.json Default License Name
    OR
    npm config get init-license
    
(6) Delete Default Values
--------------------------
==> npm config delete init-license // Delete Package.json License Value
==> npm config delete init-author-name // Delete Package.json Author Name Value
==> npm init -y // For Creating The Package.json And Check If Values Is Deleted

